2. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The maximum set packing problem is a combinatorial optimization problem and falls under the scope of discrete mathematics.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): Local search algorithms are commonly used in artificial intelligence for solving optimization problems. The paper proposes a variant of a local search algorithm for the maximum set packing problem, which could be of interest to researchers in this field.
4. cs.CC (Computational Complexity): The paper discusses the performance guarantee of the proposed local search algorithm, which is related to the computational complexity of the problem. This could be of interest to researchers in computational complexity theory.
